    "created_at": "2015-07-30T09:39:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-30T09:39:47Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It is quite a common issue: `colorama` had this issue (https://github.com/tartley/colorama/issues/32), and `progress` has also this issue (https://github.com/verigak/progress/issues/21). I think it shouldn't be assumed that `sys.std*` don't change. There are even `sys.__std*__` attributes capturing the original streams.\n\nI have no idea what else would a change affect, so I'd naively propose to change `utils.io.IOStream` so that instead of a stream, one may give it function returning a stream, so its `stream` attribute becomes a property resolving the stream at runtime. Also, all references to `utils.encoging.DEFAULT_ENCODING` could be changed to an actual call to `utils.encoding.getdefaultencoding`.\n"
  },
