    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We should be able to get rid of our `io.std*` objects on the way to 5.0 - see #9141 and #9118.\n\nWhile investigating this, I found that pyreadline, which `io.stdout` and `io.stderr` redirect through on Windows, uses WriteConsoleW:\n\nhttps://github.com/pyreadline/pyreadline/blob/4e4b7b468cfdf2dfef8e2c8c695a64e96c514213/pyreadline/console/console.py#L372\n\nThat may be of professional interest to you for win_unicode_console :-)\n"
  },
